comment: Gasol (MEM) makes incidental contact with Nurkic (DEN) during rebounding.
Jokic (DEN) makes incidental contact with Green (MEM) that does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Ennis (MEM) makes incidental contact with Harris (DEN) that does not affect his SQBR.
Harris (DEN) throws the basketball off the leg of Ennis (MEM) on a pass attempt.
Green (MEM) is established in the path of Harris (DEN) on the drive to basket.
[Observable in enhanced video] Conley (MEM) moves his pivot foot on the spin move.
Conley (MEM) is established in the path of of Mudiay (DEN) on the drive to the basket.
Harris (DEN) hand checks Conley (MEM) and affects his SQBR.
Harris (DEN) makes contact with the arm of Conley (MEM) that affects his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] Mudiay (DEN) gathers the ball with his left foot in the air, plants it (his first step), and then takes two more steps.
Gasol (MEM) sets the screen on Harris (DEN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Carter (MEM) inbounds the ball within 5 seconds.
Mudiay (DEN) makes incidental contact with Ennis (MEM) that does not affect his SQBR.
Conley (MEM) makes contact with Jokic (DEN) as he runs forward for the inbound, but does not affect his ability to get to the pass.

Angles reviewed in the Replay Center appeared to show Mudiay (DEN) touch the ball prior to it going out of bounds. The call on the floor was therefore confirmed as MEM possession. However, upon review of an additional angle postgame, it was determined that Mudiay did not touch the ball and possession should have been awarded to DEN.
Ennis (MEM) and Faried (DEN) engage for position prior to the inbound.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the shot by Gasol (MEM) was released prior to time expiring in the quarter and the ruling on the floor was upheld.
